@node SETQ
@section SETQ

TYPE: builtin @*
SYNTAX: @code{(setq SYMBOL VALUE)}@*
@sp 1
Assigns VALUE to SYMBOL in the enclosing, current scope, possibly
creating it if it doesn't already exist.

Variables with the same name in upper scopes with the same name are
not touched and continue to exist.

@example
limo > (scope (setq x 1) 
              (scope (setq x 2) 
                     (write x)) 
              (write x))
2
1
-> 1
@end example

